Equipment quality becomes apparent immediately. "Included" ski gear typically means rental equipment that gets rotated through hundreds of users each season. Boots rarely fit properly because sizing runs limited and staff lacks time for proper fitting with high-volume turnover. Skis tend toward older models with basic tune-ups that affect performance on varied Colorado snow conditions.

